        "title": "fix(dispatch): forward channel-owned progress callbacks in all chat types when verbose is off",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Forward quiet channel-owned progress callbacks in group/channel sessions, not only direct chats.\n- Keep default text tool summaries and `onToolResult` suppressed under `/verbose off`.\n- Add regression coverage for the source-delivery-suppressed group path used by native preview lanes.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts -t 'channel-owned group progress callbacks|direct native progress callbacks'`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `/verbose off` no longer suppresses channel-owned progress callbacks before Telegram can update its native preview lane.\n\nReal environment tested: Telegram bot-to-bot QA group, SUT gateway from this PR checkout, mock OpenAI provider.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node /home/obviyus/.codex/skills/custom/telegram-e2e-bot-to-bot/scripts/run-mock-sut-e2e.mjs --gateway-port 19989 --mock-port 19992 --text '@{sut} Please answer with OPENCLAW_E2E_OK_{run} only.' --expect OPENCLAW_E2E_OK --timeout-ms 90000`\n\nEvidence after fix: driver message `22134`, SUT reply `22135`, `mockRequests: 1`.\n\nObserved result after fix: SUT replied in-thread with `OPENCLAW_E2E_OK`; the request reached the model turn path through Telegram.\n\nWhat was not tested: live Slack. Discord live proof is attached in an existing PR comment.\n\nCloses #87612",
